gov.usgs.anss.edge

Class RawInputClient

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.usgs.anss.edge.RawInputClient

  • public class RawInputClient
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is a client to a RawInputServer which submits in the clear data to a edge or cwb combination. Which is chosen depends on whether the age of the data exceeds 10 days.

      • send

        public void send(java.lang.String seedname,
                 int nsamp,
                 int[] samples,
                 java.util.GregorianCalendar time,
                 double rate,
                 int activity,
                 int ioClock,
                 int quality,
                 int timingQuality)
          throws java.net.UnknownHostException
        Send a block of data to the Edge/CWB combination. If an IOException is thrown, this routine will loop and try to reopen the socket every second to send the data.
        Parameters:
        seedname - The 12 character seedname of the channel NNSSSSSCCCLL fixed format
        nsamp - The number of data samples
        samples - An int array with the samples
        time - With the time of the first sample
        rate - The data rate in Hertz
        activity - The activity flags per the SEED manual
        ioClock - The IO/CLOCK flags per the SEED manual
        quality - The data Quality flags per the SEED manual
        timingQuality - The overall timing quality (must be 0-100)
        Throws:
        java.net.UnknownHostException - - if the socket will not open
